cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SD, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language acquisition and the use of statistical dependencies between speech and non-linguistic multimodal input to bootstrap language learning. It is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it describes a neural network model that can learn word segments and their meanings. Additionally, cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possible sub-category as the model uses visual input to learn word meanings. cs.SD (Sound) is another possible sub-category as the model deals with acoustic input. Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible sub-category as the model is a neural network.
